\b \cf2 Directions
\b0 \
\
Heat 1 tbsp. oil in skillet over medium-high heat.\'a0 Add beef and cook until well-browned, about 4-5 minutes.\'a0 Remove beef from pan and set aside.\'a0\
\
Add garlic, scallions and 1 tbsp. oil in pan with beef drippings.\'a0 Cook one minute, stirring frequently.\'a0 Add broccoli and cover for 5 minutes.\
\
In a small mixing bowl, combine water and cornstarch and mix until no longer lumpy.\'a0\
\
Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger and red pepper flakes in a medium bowl.\'a0 Add cornstarch mixture and stir to combine.\'a0 Set aside.\
\
Remove cover from pan and add sauce.\'a0 Cook until sauce starts to thicken, about 3-5 minutes.\'a0 Add beef and stir to combine, cooking an additional 2-3 minutes.\
\
